Introduction

Lee Jaeyoon is the lead vocalist and dancer of the boy group SF9 under FNC Entertainment. Growing up in the countryside of Busan, South Korea, Jaeyoon is known for having a Satoori accent and even having deep knowledge about plants and animals. Jaeyoon has sang OSTs such as for the drama “Girls Generation 1979” and "My Only Love Song".

He debuted as a member of SF9 on October 5, 2016 with the group's first single album "Feeling Sensation".
